              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "First screencast on my new project: "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://github.com/akkartik/teliva"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\n\n"
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://archive.org/details/akkartik-2021-11-14"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\n\nIt's been great fun to work with a language implementation as small and elegant as Lua's. The editing environment benefits from runtime information in deciding how to present things to the programmer, and rendering a single function at a time allows me to use a simple, low-featured editor -- which in turn helps keep the implementation small and elegant."
              }
            ]
          }
